                      (chuckles)

11:19.379 --> 11:20.479
                    Good luck to
                    you, son.   

11:20.547 --> 11:22.247
        You're gonna need it.   

11:28.588 --> 11:30.189
              Eh.               

11:30.256 --> 11:31.523
    I bet that wouldn't have    
            happened            

11:31.591 --> 11:33.525
    if he'd named one           
        of his kids Sam.        

11:35.261 --> 11:37.196
        Yeah, Sam.              

11:38.531 --> 11:40.466
             So how's that paper
                route coming?   

11:40.533 --> 11:42.468
Oh, I've been                   
saving up.                      

11:42.535 --> 11:44.737
Why don't we pull over          
here to this market,            

11:44.804 --> 11:46.739
and I'll run in                 
and buy us a soda.              

11:46.806 --> 11:47.906
My treat.                       

11:47.974 --> 11:50.009
                Great idea, son.

11:50.076 --> 11:51.210
      I'll be right back.       

11:51.277 --> 11:54.179
                      Okeydokey.

11:54.247 --> 11:55.347
          (door shuts)          

11:55.415 --> 11:59.418
            (laughs)            
 He's got that Malone swagger.  

11:59.486 --> 12:03.322
     (indistinct shouting)      

12:03.390 --> 12:04.323
Floor it, Dad!                  

12:04.391 --> 12:05.324
             Why, what happened?

12:05.392 --> 12:06.625
      I robbed the store!       

12:06.693 --> 12:07.893
        (alarm ringing)         
            But why?            

12:07.961 --> 12:09.128
     I had to do something      
        to make up              

12:09.195 --> 12:10.496
      for the lack of love      
      between you and Mom.      

12:10.563 --> 12:13.699
Now move your fat ass,          
you stupid idiot!               
        (siren wailing)         

12:13.767 --> 12:15.668
         Why'd you two          
    even have a kid anyway?     

12:15.735 --> 12:17.870
    Well, we sort of thought    
          it'd be fun.          

12:17.937 --> 12:19.071
              Fun?              

12:19.139 --> 12:20.005
    I'll show you fun.          

12:21.041 --> 12:22.908
(gunshots)                      
                     Oh, no, no!

12:22.976 --> 12:24.243
         (tires screeching)     
I got one!                      

12:24.310 --> 12:25.978
Boy, did you see                
that guy's head explode?        

12:26.046 --> 12:28.414
Whoa, these hollow point bullets
        are great!              

12:29.582 --> 12:30.783
Hey, everybody!                 

12:30.850 --> 12:32.785
I'm little Sammy Malone!        

12:32.852 --> 12:35.087
And my dad                      
was a Major League pitcher!     

12:35.155 --> 12:38.157
And he didn't love              
my mother!                      

12:38.224 --> 12:41.794
(laughing maniacally)           

12:41.861 --> 12:43.929
              Oh!               

12:47.334 --> 12:50.369
            (device whirring)   

12:55.108 --> 12:57.409
Okay, Sam, I give in.           

12:57.477 --> 13:00.713
If it's a boy,                  
we can name him Sam.            

13:02.682 --> 13:04.283
              Sam?              

13:09.189 --> 13:12.057
        Sam? Sam?               

13:12.125 --> 13:13.659
            Oh, oh!             

13:13.727 --> 13:15.961
         (tapping door)         
              Oh!               

13:23.003 --> 13:23.969
         (door opening)         

13:24.070 --> 13:25.838
Here we go, darling.            

13:29.242 --> 13:30.609
                      I'm sorry.

13:30.677 --> 13:32.044
                 I hope I didn't
                ruin the moment.

13:34.014 --> 13:35.748
            Just, I was standing
          out in the hall naked.

13:35.849 --> 13:36.815
                The door slammed
              shut, and I didn't

13:36.883 --> 13:38.050
                  have any place
                     else to go.

13:38.118 --> 13:39.752
        Anyway, if you... if you
      could just loan me a robe,

13:39.819 --> 13:41.353
            I... I can wait back
                out in the hall.

13:41.421 --> 13:43.422
No, no, there's a robe you      
    can use in the bathroom.    

13:43.523 --> 13:45.157
Larry will go look for...       

13:45.225 --> 13:46.325
what's his name--               
Sam?                            
                      Sam.      

13:46.393 --> 13:47.659
                Sam-- oh, you   
                 can't miss him.

13:47.727 --> 13:51.330
            He's a big galoot   
             with a lantern jaw.

13:51.398 --> 13:53.666
        Have you ever been naked
             in a hotel hallway?

13:53.733 --> 13:56.068
        The sailors just come   
            out of the woodwork.

13:59.239 --> 14:01.340
Don't worry, miss, I'll         
find him and come right back.   

14:01.408 --> 14:03.308
                        REBECCA:
            See, I was in the   
         bathroom taking a bath,

14:03.376 --> 14:04.777
                     and I-I was
                 talking to Sam,

14:04.844 --> 14:06.378
            but he wasn't really
        even listening to me.   

14:06.446 --> 14:07.780
                     I mean, I-I
                guess he decided

14:07.847 --> 14:10.149
     to go down to the store and
      get some gum or something.

14:10.216 --> 14:12.017
            I don't know, and it
        was... it was like he...

14:12.085 --> 14:15.721
             he didn't even know
            that I was... alive.

14:21.127 --> 14:23.128
         Boy, you sure          
        look beautiful.         

14:23.196 --> 14:24.329
            (gasps)             

14:24.397 --> 14:27.399
Oh! Look at                     
all these flowers.              

14:27.467 --> 14:30.669
Oh, my... boy, you must         
have a huge family.             

14:30.737 --> 14:33.038
                No, those are   
                all from my guy.

14:33.106 --> 14:34.540
                 Isn't he sweet?

14:34.607 --> 14:36.508
    Wow.                        

14:36.576 --> 14:37.710
Well, mine's down               
right now,                      

14:37.777 --> 14:39.144
getting me some, uh,            

14:39.212 --> 14:42.414
gum... I think.                 

14:42.482 --> 14:44.416
How long have you and Sam       
         been married?          

14:44.484 --> 14:46.385
        Oh, actually, we        
      weren't even plan...      

14:46.453 --> 14:48.187
          Six months.           

14:48.254 --> 14:50.089
         (phone rings)          
                      Excuse me.

14:50.156 --> 14:51.256
                          Hello?

14:51.324 --> 14:52.758
                  Oh, hi, honey.

14:52.826 --> 14:53.892
                It's my husband.

14:53.960 --> 14:56.028
He's already down in the lobby? 

14:56.096 --> 14:57.796
      No, he's calling me       
    from the elevator phone     

14:57.864 --> 14:59.231
  just to tell me he loves me.  

15:00.834 --> 15:02.134
             It's supposed to be
        just for emergencies.   

15:02.202 --> 15:05.204
        Oh, you are so sweet.   

15:05.271 --> 15:09.475
Oh, you're the                  
perfect couple, aren't you?     

15:09.542 --> 15:11.910
         Oh, I bet you          
    had a beautiful wedding.    

15:11.978 --> 15:13.145
Oh, well,                       
all weddings are nice.          

15:13.213 --> 15:14.279
Wasn't yours?                   

15:14.347 --> 15:15.881
        Oh, yeah.               

15:15.949 --> 15:18.150
    We had, you know,           
        lots of flowe...        

15:18.218 --> 15:20.085
      and we had... a lot       
      of people came in...      

15:20.153 --> 15:21.920
    (voice breaking):           
        a lot of people         
    from out of town.           

15:24.958 --> 15:26.158
                If you'll excuse
                    me a minute,

15:26.226 --> 15:28.127
             I'm just gonna wait
            outside in the hall.

15:30.830 --> 15:32.031
                  Oh, hi.       

15:32.098 --> 15:33.198
                Um, there's a   
                 bellboy waiting

15:33.266 --> 15:34.500
            outside your room   
                 with a passkey.

15:34.567 --> 15:35.567
             Okay.              

15:35.669 --> 15:37.436
                Sorry I couldn't
              find your husband.

15:37.504 --> 15:39.938
                But look what   
                     I did find!

15:40.006 --> 15:42.641
          Oh, a bunny!          

15:47.947 --> 15:51.583
You have the sweetest lips in   
    the whole wide world, honey!

15:57.457 --> 16:00.526
             Mmm, you've got the
            sweetest lips in the
        whole wide world, honey.

16:00.593 --> 16:02.361
         (door opening)         

16:02.429 --> 16:04.630
Knock-knock! The little         
woman is home.                  

16:04.698 --> 16:05.864
            Hey!                

16:05.932 --> 16:07.800
What are you                    
barging in here for?            

16:07.867 --> 16:10.269
    You forgot to hang          
     the sock on the door.      

16:10.337 --> 16:12.571
    That's because I didn't     
      want to take it off.      

16:12.639 --> 16:14.473
          It was cold.          
They turned the heat off.       

16:14.541 --> 16:15.874
Oh, yeah, they turned           
the heat off                    

16:15.942 --> 16:17.576
'cause you forgot               
to pay the bill, pal!           

16:17.677 --> 16:20.145
      What was I supposed       
     to pay it with-- love?     

16:20.213 --> 16:21.780
Oh shut up.                     
                No, you shut!   

16:21.848 --> 16:22.948
            You shut!           
    Shut...                     

16:23.016 --> 16:24.983
                     Shut... up!
  Shut...!                      

16:28.621 --> 16:29.955
         Come on, Sam,          
      get her out of here.      

16:30.023 --> 16:31.090
         I'm ovulating.         

16:31.191 --> 16:34.226
            Oh, that's great.   

16:34.294 --> 16:37.429
      You couldn't tell me      
        15 minutes ago?         

16:37.497 --> 16:39.231
    Come on, scooch, honey.     

16:39.299 --> 16:42.534
I've got my chores to do.       

16:42.602 --> 16:45.237
          Yeah, go on, go on, go
            on, go on, go on.   

16:45.338 --> 16:47.272
  Oh, Sam, come on, hurry up,   
    let's make a baby!          

16:47.340 --> 16:49.041
     Let's go in the other      
        room and do it!         

16:49.109 --> 16:51.176
This is the other room.         

16:52.746 --> 16:55.347
     Oh God! Why are we so      
      poor and miserable?       

16:55.415 --> 16:57.082
  Well, honey, we may be poor   
         and miserable,         

16:57.150 --> 16:59.218
    but at least we can live    
            on love!            

16:59.285 --> 17:01.620
          You shut up!          

17:01.721 --> 17:02.721
        Oh, you shut up!        
No, you shut up!                

17:02.856 --> 17:03.989
                     Shut me up!

17:04.057 --> 17:05.691
    Shut up!                    
                     Shut up!   

17:07.594 --> 17:09.060
Don't you use                   
that word "love."               

17:09.128 --> 17:10.896
     Love has nothing to do     
    with this relationship!     

17:10.964 --> 17:12.664
I will use any word I want      
         in this house!         

17:12.732 --> 17:13.766
             Love!              

17:13.833 --> 17:14.800
                     Love, love,
                     love, love,

17:14.867 --> 17:15.901
    love, love, love!           

17:15.969 --> 17:17.935
 You foul-mouthed barren tramp! 

17:18.003 --> 17:19.238
      Half man! Half man!       

17:19.406 --> 17:21.674
         (Sam grunting)         

17:25.011 --> 17:27.279
    Enough foreplay for you?    

17:27.347 --> 17:29.815
Yeah. Turn off the light.       

17:29.916 --> 17:32.951
        I've got a poker game on
     that table in five minutes.

17:33.019 --> 17:34.386
     You'd better make it quick.

17:34.454 --> 17:36.522
        Oh, yeah, that's        
    gonna be tough with you.    

17:36.589 --> 17:38.590
        Hey, shut up!           
                You shut up!    

17:38.658 --> 17:39.758
You shut up!                    

17:39.826 --> 17:40.826
Shut!                           
                Shut!           

17:40.894 --> 17:42.461
             BOTH:              
            Shut up!            

17:47.233 --> 17:48.934
Could you leave now?            

17:49.002 --> 17:50.436
        Oh, sure.               

17:58.945 --> 18:00.779
                    Hey.        

18:00.847 --> 18:03.382
      Why aren't you home       
watching your scabby kid?       

18:05.819 --> 18:08.554
My mother's come into town      
to help take care of him.       

18:08.621 --> 18:11.056
  So I thought I'd steal a few  
     moments and come here      

18:11.124 --> 18:12.324
and relax with my husband.      

18:12.392 --> 18:13.359
         He's not here.         

18:13.426 --> 18:15.294
          Better yet.           

18:16.796 --> 18:18.964
Where is my husband,            
anyway?                         

18:19.032 --> 18:20.532
    Oh, uh, some of the guys    

18:20.600 --> 18:22.835
     went to do something,      
    and he went along.          

18:22.902 --> 18:27.172
I suppose if they all           
went to jump off a cliff        
he'd do that, too.              

18:27.240 --> 18:29.708
  I, didn't think of that, but  
 it probably would have worked. 

18:31.144 --> 18:32.945
          (chanting):           
          Polar Bear!           

18:33.013 --> 18:34.580
    Polar Bear! Polar Bear!     

18:35.882 --> 18:37.349
     Hey, so you guys went      
     for your little swim?      

18:37.417 --> 18:39.018
            Yeah, well, we drove
        down there, you know,   

18:39.085 --> 18:40.853
              we jumped into our
            bathing suits, uh...

18:40.920 --> 18:42.154
        raced each other        
        along the beach         

18:42.222 --> 18:43.355
our feet hit the water...       

18:43.423 --> 18:44.990
 And you chickened out, right?  

18:45.058 --> 18:46.558
        Yeah, well, we prefer   
                  to think of it

18:46.626 --> 18:48.660
                as coming to our
             senses just in time
            to save our goodies.

18:51.197 --> 18:53.465
So none of you guys had the guts
  to go through with it, huh?   

18:53.533 --> 18:55.300
    Well, uh, one of us did.    

18:59.606 --> 19:01.540
                 Just a few more
            steps, Dr. Crane.   

19:03.176 --> 19:04.910
  Darling, are you all right?   

19:04.978 --> 19:06.145
        (whimpers)              

19:06.212 --> 19:08.047
What did he say?                

19:08.114 --> 19:09.948
         Sounded like "oil can."

19:12.152 --> 19:14.853
Here, this should               
help warm you up.               

19:17.624 --> 19:20.125
It must have been               
a terrifying experience.        

19:20.193 --> 19:21.326
              Oh!               

19:21.394 --> 19:24.530
It was positively surreal.      

19:24.597 --> 19:27.933
 First, the cold water hitting  
  me like an electric shock...  

19:28.001 --> 19:30.336
     dragging me down like      
    a palpable force.           

19:30.403 --> 19:33.872
  And then when I was crawling  
      back onto the beach,      

19:33.940 --> 19:36.342
it kept at me, as though,       
    for all the world,          

19:36.409 --> 19:40.913
someone was actually pushing me 
  back into the frozen water.   

19:40.980 --> 19:43.515
Told you                        
it wasn't funny.                

19:58.965 --> 20:01.600
Where have you been, Sam?       

20:01.668 --> 20:03.369
                    Just, uh,   
                went for a walk,

20:03.436 --> 20:05.671
        you know, to get some   
    fresh air and everything.   

20:05.739 --> 20:08.741
          So... ready           
    to make the baby?           

20:08.808 --> 20:11.377
     Sure I am, if you are.     

20:11.444 --> 20:12.845
                    Oh, you are?

20:12.912 --> 20:14.980
                 Uh, well, yeah.
                All right, good.

20:15.048 --> 20:16.682
                 Let's... let's,
                 get to it here.

20:16.750 --> 20:17.816
    Okay.                       

20:21.821 --> 20:26.558
    Okay, let's, let's, uh,     
     let's make that baby.      

20:26.626 --> 20:29.862
There's something wrong         
isn't there, Sam?               

20:32.032 --> 20:34.700
  Uh, yeah, there's something   
    I want to say and I-I...    

20:34.768 --> 20:36.969
    I've been walking around    
      trying to figure out      

20:37.037 --> 20:39.238
  how to say it and I, I guess  
      the only thing to do      

20:39.305 --> 20:40.773
        is just, say it.        

20:40.840 --> 20:42.975
     Sam, I don't love you.     
 I'm not gonna have your baby.  

20:43.043 --> 20:44.309
          It would be           
     a big, stupid mistake.     

20:44.377 --> 20:45.477
             What?              

20:45.545 --> 20:48.280
    What were you gonna say?    

20:48.348 --> 20:52.351
     Well, the same thing,      
     but a much nicer way.      

20:53.787 --> 20:55.087
You were?                       

20:55.155 --> 20:56.655
                        Yeah.   

20:56.723 --> 20:59.258
         I mean, you know, if we
          don't love each other,

20:59.325 --> 21:00.659
         how can we raise a kid?

21:00.727 --> 21:01.794
That's right!                   

21:01.861 --> 21:03.796
     Because it wouldn't be     
        fair to the kid.        

21:03.863 --> 21:05.831
                  I agree.      
I mean, I mean, all             
we've talked about              

21:05.899 --> 21:07.833
is how much we want             
a baby. We, we, we.             

21:07.901 --> 21:09.168
We never even                   
thought about...                

21:09.235 --> 21:11.337
about how it would be           
for a baby to have us.          
                  I agree.      

21:11.404 --> 21:13.772
I mean, I think we got          
to call the whole thing off.    
                Oh, I agree!    

21:13.840 --> 21:15.074
        I can't believe this!   

21:15.141 --> 21:16.642
         This is the first thing
              we've agreed about

21:16.710 --> 21:18.143
            since the whole baby
                  thing came up.

21:18.211 --> 21:19.878
        I agree!                

21:19.946 --> 21:21.947
Oh, Sam I love you!             
            Oh, I love you, too!

21:22.015 --> 21:23.182
I mean, I don't                 
"love you," love you.           

21:23.249 --> 21:25.150
         No, I don't "love you,"
            love you, either.   

21:25.218 --> 21:27.953
And Sam, we can still have kids,
just not with each other.       

21:28.021 --> 21:29.288
                Yeah.           

21:36.162 --> 21:37.529
         Mm.                    
            Mm-mm. I'm sorry.   

21:37.597 --> 21:39.164
                  Old habit.    

21:39.232 --> 21:41.667
That's right,                   
we're just friends.             

21:41.735 --> 21:44.203
          Yeah. Actually friends
        don't open their mouths.

21:44.270 --> 21:46.638
    Oh. Old habit.              

21:50.076 --> 21:51.310
            (sighs)             

21:54.147 --> 21:56.548
See you at work                 
tomorrow.                       

21:56.616 --> 21:57.883
             Yeah.              

21:57.951 --> 21:59.752
            Bye-bye.            

22:16.870 --> 22:18.971
     Sam, what's happening?     

22:19.039 --> 22:20.572
See you in a couple years, Dad. 

22:20.640 --> 22:21.807
              Sam?              

22:21.875 --> 22:24.643
Where are you going?            

22:24.711 --> 22:27.546
              Sam?              

22:43.163 --> 22:44.797
                 You rotten kid!

22:44.864 --> 22:46.498
            Now listen, bring   
                 back my wallet!

22:46.566 --> 22:48.233
KID:                            
You're beginning                
to waddle!                      

